From 3919d19471900df88095a239b04265bdf5c4d79d Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Nadia Yvette Chambers <nadia.yvette.chambers@ik.me>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 14:46:34 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 171/174] mm/khugepaged: disable file/shmem THP collapse under
 PGCL

Anon PTE collapse (hpage_collapse_scan_pmd) and try_collapse_pte_mapped_thp
are already #if PAGE_MMUSHIFT-disabled: collapse assumes PAGE_SIZE ==
MMUPAGE_SIZE throughout (HPAGE_PMD_NR iteration counts, PAGE_SIZE strides,
PAGE-granular copy helpers).  collapse_file() was left active but shares the
flaw -- it counts/iterates in HPAGE_PMD_NR/PAGE_SIZE units while the PGCL
page cache is cluster(PAGE)-indexed and rmap mapcount + MM_FILEPAGES rss are
MMUPAGE-granular.  Collapsing a file mapping therefore corrupts the file
folio mapcount/refcount (the laptop "Bad page map" page-cache corruption
class) and trips VM_BUG_ON(start & (HPAGE_PMD_NR-1)) at the top of
collapse_file when start is a mismatched-unit pgoff.

Disable collapse_file() under PGCL (return SCAN_FAIL) until ported, mirroring
the anon disable; it is the single chokepoint for both khugepaged scan and
MADV_COLLAPSE.  File THP collapse is a TLB optimization, never required for
correctness, and is largely redundant with PGCL clustering.  Identity at
PAGE_MMUSHIFT==0.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.8 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01UkhHXA2PvPb3uwymHGbYh8
---
 mm/khugepaged.c | 14 ++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 14 insertions(+)

diff --git a/mm/khugepaged.c b/mm/khugepaged.c
index 631872368242..4942cb2e351c 100644
--- a/mm/khugepaged.c
+++ b/mm/khugepaged.c
@@ -1911,6 +1911,20 @@ static enum scan_result collapse_file(struct mm_struct *mm, unsigned long addr,
 	int nr_none = 0;
 	bool is_shmem = shmem_file(file);
 
+#if PAGE_MMUSHIFT
+	/*
+	 * See comment in hpage_collapse_scan_pmd(): file/shmem THP collapse is
+	 * not yet ported to sub-PAGE (MMUPAGE) granularity.  Under PGCL the page
+	 * cache xarray is cluster (PAGE)-indexed and rmap mapcount + MM_FILEPAGES
+	 * rss are MMUPAGE-granular, but this collapser counts in HPAGE_PMD_NR /
+	 * PAGE_SIZE units -- corrupting the file folio mapcount/refcount and
+	 * leaking MM_FILEPAGES rss (observed: "Bad page map" mapcount underflow
+	 * and "Bad rss-counter state").  The HPAGE_PMD_NR-alignment VM_BUG_ON
+	 * below is itself the file-collapse #121 crash.  Disable until ported.
+	 */
+	return SCAN_FAIL;
+#endif
+
 	VM_BUG_ON(!IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_READ_ONLY_THP_FOR_FS) && !is_shmem);
 	VM_BUG_ON(start & (HPAGE_PMD_NR - 1));
 
